3. How to solve the "I know who said it" problem
To prevent the tutor from knowing exactly which student "said crap" about them, use these two rules:
 * The 24-Hour Delay: Do not show the comment to the tutor immediately. Only show it 24 to 48 hours after the session is over. By then, the tutor has likely seen 10+ other students, making it harder to pin the comment on one person.
 * Topic Masking: In the Tutor‚Äôs view, hide the specific topic (e.g., "Solve for X"). Instead, display a broader category (e.g., "Mathematics").
Why this is the best choice:
 * Protects the Student: The student can be honest without fear of the tutor being mean to them in the next session.
