To make this work professionally in your code, don't just "add" a rating. Use the student's UID as the Document ID inside a ratings sub-collection under the tutor.
Why? Because in Firebase, if you write to the same Document ID, it overwrites the old data.
The Code Logic:
 * Student finishes session.
 * System checks if ratings/[student_uid] exists for this tutor.
 * Student submits rating -> setDoc (not addDoc).
 * Result: The old rating is gone, the new one is there. Cost = 1 Write.
